text.tspan: Natural population growth rate vs. child mortality rate, 2021
The child mortality rate measures the share of children who die before reaching the age of five. In this metric of
population growth, changes due to migration are excluded and only births and deaths are considered.
Data source: United Nations, World Population Prospects (2022)
